Code Explanation and other clarifications

  1. For Cilk I used cilk_spawn and cilk_sync() and for openMP #pragma omp parallel and #pragma omp task, to parallelise the recursive calls.
  2. In pthread, I created an array of pthread_t and an int array of the same length(if the cell is 1, then the thread is currently in use). Each time i want to create a thread, i call findAvailableThreads(). This function checks the int array for an available thread, and returns either the index of the thread or -1. If -1 is returned, then the recursion is done sequential, until there is a thread available.Pthread only parallelises the recursion call.
  3. Pthread_9000 also parallelises the partion. The ‘main’ thread does partition for the first half of the array , and the ‘new’ thread does inverse-partition for the other-half. Then each thread waits for the other to finish and the final swaps are made.
